# Contributing

Thanks for offering your time, brain power, and finger strokes to this project.

## Support questions

Please don't submit support questions to the issue tracker, instead using the
mailing list or StackOverflow.

## Reporting Issues

Try to be as detailed as possible. Include the library version, Python
interpreter version, operating system, and any additional information like
tracebacks.

## Submitting Patches

Try to follow PEP8 where it makes sense. Include tests for patches that fix bug
and make sure your tests fail without your patch.

## Running the test suite

We use tox for this project, setup a virtual environment `pip install tox` then
run `tox`.
